        "subject": "LU-993 tests: remove redundant sanity test_51c",
        "message": "LU-993 tests: remove redundant sanity test_51c\n\nWhen the patch in change Id02e7d2ac3a7664a55566b1de783f0a73162339b\nfor handling nlink counting in osd-ldiskfs was landed, it added a\nnew sanity.sh test_51ba() which deleted all of the subdirs created\nin test_51a().  However, test_51c() was also expecting to delete\nthose subdirs, and now fails on every SLOW=yes test run (it is\nexcluded from normal review test runs).\n\nRename test_51ba() to test_51c(), since it largely does the same\nthings, but with a bit more checking, and delete the old test_51c.\n\nSigned-off-by: Andreas Dilger <adilger@whamcloud.com>\nChange-Id: Ia6311ea5d84c83866033c3f92fa125834f48cab0\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
